cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with Grammatical Error Correction (GEC) and proposes a method to combine different GEC systems. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the proposed method involves automatic detection of the strength of a system or combination of systems per error type, which involves machine learning techniques. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with improving the performance of GEC systems using automatic methods. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is less likely but still possible as the paper proposes a method to optimize the F score directly, which could be relevant in robotics applications. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also less likely but possible as the paper describes a system submission to a shared task and proposes a new spellchecker for GEC.
